				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That really depends, Rsak, on whether or not the territory is truly "occupied" or not. Sure, we claim it's occupied, but many of the areas experiencing the insurgencies were never really under control, and thus they'd fall under the Geneva Convention as defined in Section 4, I believe. The same rule applies if they're Iraqi army regulars whether or not they're fighting during an occupation.
<br />

<br />
And besides that, many to most of those imprisoned are either A) innovent civilians, or B) Iraqi army regulars who definitely DO fall under the GC or C) others who were captured prior to the farcical declaration of victory who also fall under the GC.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
