			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I will admit that the Geneva Conventions is not very specific on what a regular armed force is. It only describes it in context in the convention. 
<br />

<br />
I do believe that regular armed forces require there to be diplomatic channels and contacts if not formal declaration of war. 
<br />

<br />
However this is moot because if former iraqi military have discarded their uniforms and become insurgents then they are violating the rules of war by targetting civilians and committing acts of terrorism. 
<br />

<br />
This disqualifies them from being regular armed forces which have to follow these rules. 
<br />

<br />
Insurgents found in Iraq under no possiblity are entitled to the rights as prisoners of war.<br />_________________<br />/hugs
