<br />
And here's one to bake your noodle: The US declared victory before securing the country. Does the declaration of victory change these people from defenders to insurgents regardless of whether the invasion is complete and the nation is truly under occupation?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Considering that, at the outset (things have changed a little), the "insurgents" were not remnants Baathist party elements, but rather a "new" organization within the country (by new, I mean an organization that had no political control of the country before the invasion), I would consider the initial resistance to be an insurgency.
<br />

<br />
However, things have turned aa bit more opaque since then.  Elements of the former Baathist party military have joined in an uneasy alliance with the initial insurgents, and are mounting a more coordinated, sophisticated resistance.  
<br />

<br />
Does this turn the initial insurgents into defenders?  Or the Baathist defenders into insurgents?<br />_________________<br />Embar
<br />
Alarius</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
