<br />
They are trying to enforce a change in government to something different from the current government and the past one. They are not defending anything and do not belong to any signatory group of the geneva conventions. 
<br />

<br />
That does not stop the general protections of the geneva conventions from applying, but it does not allow them to be granted a regular armed forces status or entitled to prisoner of war status as prisoners. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Others are sticking to military targets.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
